<br>
The reason that deterrence works is fear, the reason why there was no nuclear war between the US and USSR was fear, we both could annihilate the other if we pursued our national interests vigorously, therefore, instead both sides backed down, and instead made it their interest to oppose the other in ways short of war.<br>
<br>
And the 'fear' works both ways, if two small nations both know that if they go to war with their neighbor that the US will come down on them like a load of bricks, and conversely knows that if their neighbor goes to war with them that the US will come down on their neighbor like a load of bricks, and thus knows that neither them nor their neighbor could possibly win any conflict, might they not then be more amenable to peaceful settlement, knowing that there is a hegemonic force in the wings expecting them to do so?  Or would it be more moral for the two nations to go to war with each other and slaughter thousands of people so that the US can feel good about not making people scared of it?<br>
<br>
Is it more 'moral' to permit war and violence to reign unchecked throughout the world or to increase your own power to the point where the mere threat of you intervening keeps the peace?  Is it somehow wrong for dictators and tyrants to fear the consequences of their actions?  A moral hegemon is one who makes use of its power to further moral goals, and peaceful coexistance is by any defination a moral goal.<br>
<br>
As far as terrorists go, the United States is hated already, irregardless of what we do, by the authoritarians and dictators of the world, and those who follow them.  We will be the target of fanatics regardless of what we do, but with an overwhelming preponderance of power and a demonstrated willingness to make use of that power, few if any nation-states will risk their own existance to sponsor and support terrorist organizations, which reduces the threat to the 'lone wackjob' category.  Sure, lone wackjobs can do damage, but they also are far more likely to get caught before they manage to pull off an attack, and are far less well equipped/trained.  All in all, a worthy tradeoff, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
It's called 'peace through superior firepower' and, historically, is far more reliable than 'peace through warm fuzzy feelings of love and happiness' <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=traxxus>Traxxus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 3:27:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Irexes...</span><hr size=1> Well said Edward <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukiluen73.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kiluen73</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 4:20:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1158.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Irexes...</span><hr size=1> Don't care much what everyone thinks or has to say on this subject.  You are all entitled to your own opinions.<br>
